  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">\"Living with History, 1914-1964,\" published by Leuven University Press in 2021, reflects a significant scholarly output in its field, although it has not yet garnered citations or mentions in social discourse platforms. The work demonstrates a strong commercial linkage with substantial availability on platforms such as Amazon and Goodreads, suggesting potential readership interest.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">\"Living with History, 1914-1964,\" released by Leuven University Press in 2021, serves as a noteworthy contribution to historical scholarship, specifically in the context of events between 1914 and 1964. Despite the absence of recorded citations and social media discussions, the work's placement on commercial platforms indicates it may reach an audience beyond academia. With a strong commercial linkage, the book is readily available on platforms like Amazon and Goodreads, suggesting a potential willingness among the public to engage with its content.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">While it has not yet established a robust academic footprint through citations or mentions in community discourse on platforms such as Wikipedia or Reddit, the book's subject matter inherently addresses significant historical themes that resonate within broader societal contexts. The social relevance is underscored by a modest sustainability and policy relevance score, indicating that the teachings within the text align with contemporary discussions about sustainability as outlined in one of the Sustainable Development Goals.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Furthermore, the inferred scholarly uptake reveals an indication that there is emerging interest from other scholars, evidenced by an initial citation count of three. This suggests a nascent engagement with the work that may develop over time as more researchers discover its insights into the historical continuum from 1914 to 1964.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Overall, while \"Living with History, 1914-1964\" navigates a challenging landscape with limited immediate online engagement, its commercial platforms and early signs of scholarly uptake indicate a potential for greater impact and integration within both academic and public discourse as it continues to be disseminated and discussed.</p>",
